\begin_inset Formula $2\pi/L$
\end_inset

.
 The convenient basis functions are
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\phi_{n\boldsymbol{p}}=\sqrt{\frac{\beta}{\mathrm{V}}}\mathrm{e}^{i\left(\boldsymbol{p}\cdot\boldsymbol{x}+\omega_{n}x^{4}\right)},
\end{equation}

\end_inset

which are normalised so that
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\Braket{\phi_{m\boldsymbol{q}}|\phi_{n\boldsymbol{p}}}=\beta^{2}\delta_{mn}\delta_{\boldsymbol{p}\boldsymbol{q}},
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where, on functions, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Braket{f|g}\equiv\int_{x_{E}}f^{\star}g$
\end_inset

.
