 Then 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\int_{x_{E}}\mathcal{L}_{E}=-\frac{1}{2}\sum_{n\boldsymbol{p}}\left|A_{n\boldsymbol{p}}\right|^{2}\beta^{2}\left(\omega_{n}^{2}+\boldsymbol{p}^{2}+m^{2}\right).
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The functional integrand does not depend on the phases of 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{n\boldsymbol{p}}$
\end_inset

